msgid "Session Files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/sessions.rst:7 bde22c575b154faeb1b4e652087def22
msgid "Contents"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/sessions.rst:9 b2c659cebd8a4d0aba401153b175734c
msgid ""
"They are an important part for the library to be efficient, such as "
"caching and handling your authorization key (or you would have to login "
"every time!)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/sessions.rst:13 d330aa5d0b554d17b9b9e2a0aa745eee
msgid "What are Sessions?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/sessions.rst:15 a8f8ca7f40dc4321b980565b46b4f42c
msgid ""
"The first parameter you pass to the constructor of the :ref:`Client "
"<grammers-client>` is the ``session``, and defaults to be the session "
"name (or full path). That is, if you create a ``Client('anon')`` instance"
" and connect, an ``anon.session`` file will be created in the working "
"directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/sessions.rst:21 9a3996ebb9404c4db2f8aab89ef4d999
msgid ""
"Note that if you pass a string it will be a file in the current working "
"directory, although you can also pass absolute paths."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/sessions.rst:24 c6a6d585629949e4b5c941a56dac744a
msgid ""
"The session file contains enough information for you to login without re-"
"sending the code, so if you have to enter the code more than once, maybe "
"you're changing the working directory, renaming or removing the file, or "
"using random names."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/sessions.rst:29 803f8dad3f5047cf8f645d56e0235d7e
msgid ""
"These database files using ``sqlite3`` contain the required information "
"to talk to the Telegram servers, such as to which IP the client should "
"connect, port, authorization key so that messages can be encrypted, and "
"so on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/sessions.rst:33 e56ee4191cad4a84bb7d6ac591bf0c24
msgid ""
"These files will by default also save all the input entities that you've "
"seen, so that you can get information about a user or channel by just "
"their ID. Telegram will **not** send their ``access_hash`` required to "
"retrieve more information about them, if it thinks you have already seem "
"them. For this reason, the library needs to store this information "
"offline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/sessions.rst:39 8e89d8b17076476096224f761f4eb41e
msgid ""
"The library will by default too save all the entities (chats and channels"
" with their name and username, and users with the phone too) in the "
"session file, so that you can quickly access them by username or phone "
"number."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/sessions.rst:50 e245e7ff19d94fbda6a9184bd262678f
msgid "Different Session Storage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/sessions.rst:52 f7cdee3aef9d4b7eb8eee99cd2ecf604
msgid ""
"If you don't want to use the default SQLite session storage, you can also"
" use one of the other implementations or implement your own storage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/sessions.rst:55 93db5c826d3247729d46cc450c026186
msgid ""
"While it's often not the case, it's possible that SQLite is slow enough "
"to be noticeable, in which case you can also use a different storage. "
"Note that this is rare and most people won't have this issue, but it's "
"worth a mention."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/sessions.rst:59 84d846525d6e495885a3987192ad4f79
msgid ""
"To use a custom session storage, simply pass the custom session instance "
"to :ref:`Client <grammers-client>` instead of the session name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/sessions.rst:63 9e2b1c24a32441e18c9fcee703eea49c
