msgid "String Sessions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/sessions.rst:84 2b5a1ccc440f40428f129b23adcba5c1
msgid ""
"`SQLiteSession.from_telethon_string() "
"<SQLiteSession.from_telethon_string>` are a convenient way to embed your "
"login credentials directly into your code for extremely easy portability,"
" since all they take is a string to be able to login without asking for "
"your phone and code (or faster start if you're using a bot token)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/sessions.rst:89 a631d4de25e9454c8abd33dc5a2723b4
msgid "The easiest way to generate a string session is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/sessions.rst:101 63c8b3e7451841d382b4da6a4d971cc1
msgid ""
"Think of this as a way to export your authorization key (what's needed to"
" login into your account). This will print a string in the standard "
"output (likely your terminal)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/sessions.rst:107 f884f81b88e84866b31b64efdba1048a
msgid ""
"**Keep this string safe!** Anyone with this string can use it to login "
"into your account and do anything they want to."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/sessions.rst:110 5a091dbd974449d0b98f5d310dd5f3dd
msgid ""
"This is similar to leaking your ``*.session`` files online, but it is "
"easier to leak a string than it is to leak a file."
msgstr ""

